William H. Lange, appellee, v. T. H. Flood & Company, appellant.Gen. No. 26,903.Assumpsit upon accounts for printing a law book. Judgment for plaintiff. Appeal from the Municipal Court of Chicago; the Hon. Charles A. Williams, Judge, presiding. Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the March term, 1921.Reversed and remanded.

Barnes, J., took no part in the decision of this ease.

Opinion filed March 21, 1922.James E. McGrath, for appellant. Charles E. Erbstein, for appellee. Mr. Justice Morrill

delivered the opinion of the court.
